The message bus configuration has 2 unbound inbound routes.
Each route below was registered but never attached to a receive endpoint.

[1] ItemShippedHandler (Mocha.Tests.MessageTypes.MessageBusConfigurationValidationTests+ItemShippedHandler)
    message : urn:message:mocha.tests.message-types:item-shipped (Mocha.Tests.MessageTypes.MessageBusConfigurationValidationTests+ItemShipped)
    kind    : Subscribe
    where   : MessageType(urn:message:mocha.tests.message-types:item-shipped)
    fix     : Transport 'memory' uses explicit bind mode, so no convention receive endpoint is created for unbound consumers. If this consumer should receive over a transport, bind it to a receive endpoint. If it is handled in-process only or superseded, remove it from message bus registration. Available default receive endpoints: none.

[2] OrderCreatedHandler (Mocha.Tests.MessageTypes.MessageBusConfigurationValidationTests+OrderCreatedHandler)
    message : urn:message:mocha.tests.message-types:order-created (Mocha.Tests.MessageTypes.MessageBusConfigurationValidationTests+OrderCreated)
    kind    : Subscribe
    where   : MessageType(urn:message:mocha.tests.message-types:order-created)
    fix     : Transport 'memory' uses explicit bind mode, so no convention receive endpoint is created for unbound consumers. If this consumer should receive over a transport, bind it to a receive endpoint. If it is handled in-process only or superseded, remove it from message bus registration. Available default receive endpoints: none.
